
Credits:
This is an exercise from the Intermezzos project http://intermezzos.github.io/
All credits to the code go to the authors of the Intermezzos project
referenced above. This work is merely a study and an implementation
of the project.

Purpose:
The project has been created in a cargo project and is designed to
launch a very simple kernel that prints "Hello Rust" in QEMU.

Pre-requsities:
- Ubunut 20.04 (If running on Virtual Box, ensure Nested Virtualization Support is enabled)
- Install Rust Language, see https://www.rust-lang.org/tools/install 
- Install QEMU-KVM on Ubuntu, see the following links for steps: (skip the network bridge configuration)
  https://linuxconfig.org/install-and-set-up-kvm-on-ubuntu-20-04-focal-fossa-linux
  https://computingforgeeks.com/install-kvm-hypervisor-on-ubuntu-focal-fossa/
  https://www.how2shout.com/how-to/how-to-install-kvm-on-ubuntu-20-04-graphical-headless-server.html
- Explicitly enable Nested Virtualization, see "Nested Virtualization" at https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/KVM 

How to run the project:
$ cargo r 
